{"title_page": "Dariusz Jemielniak", "text_new": "{{Infobox scientist\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name        = Dariusz Jemielniak\n| honorific_suffix =\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image       = Dr. Dariusz Jemielniak.jpg\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = Dariusz Jemielniak\n| caption     = Jemielniak in 2015\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1975|03|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| death_cause = \n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates =\n| other_names = \n| residence   = \n| citizenship = \n| nationality = [[Polish people|Polish]]\n| fields      = [[Economics]]\n| workplaces  = [[Kozminski University]]\n| patrons     = \n| education   = \n| alma_mater  = \n| thesis_title =        <!--(or  | thesis1_title =  and  | thesis2_title = )-->\n| thesis_url  =         <!--(or  | thesis1_url  =   and  | thesis2_url  =  )-->\n| thesis_year =         <!--(or  | thesis1_year =   and  | thesis2_year =  )-->\n| doctoral_advisor =    <!--(or  | doctoral_advisors = )-->\n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students = \n| known_for   = \n| influences  = \n| influenced  = \n| awards      = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| spouse      =         <!--(or | spouses = )-->\n| partner     =         <!--(or | partners = )-->\n| children    = \n| signature   =         <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt = \n| website     = {{URL|www.jemielniak.org}}\n| footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''Dariusz Jemielniak''' (born March 17, 1975) is a full professor of management, the head of the Center for Research on Organizations and Workplaces (CROW), and a founder of New Research on Digital Societies (NeRDS) group at [[Kozminski University]]. Van egy feles\u00e9ge, Fanni, \u00e9s 2 gyermek\u00fck. His interests revolve about [[critical management studies]], [[open collaboration]] projects (such as [[Wikipedia]] or [[F/LOSS]]), [[narrativity]], [[storytelling]], [[knowledge-intensive organizations]], [[virtual communities]], organizational archetypes, all studied by interpretive and qualitative methods.<ref>[http://crow.kozminski.edu.pl/?page_id=10 ''About us. Dariusz Jemielniak''] CROW website, accessed on 1 October 2012</ref> In 2015, he was elected to the [[Wikimedia Foundation]] board of trustees.\n\n== Career ==\nHe is a graduate of [[VI Liceum Og\u00f3lnokszta\u0142c\u0105ce im. Tadeusza Reytana w Warszawie]] and a 2000 ''[[Cum laude|summa cum laude]]'' graduate from the Faculty of Management, [[Warsaw University]]. In 2004 he earned a Ph.D. in economics from the [[Kozminski University]], under the supervision of [[Andrzej Ko\u017ami\u0144ski]]. In 2014, he received his [[Professor]]'s degree from the [[President of Poland]].\n\nHe has researched and published books in the field of work-space studies; about [[IT professionals]]<ref>[http://www.informationweek.in/Software/10-06-28/Software_engineers_doubt_competence_of_Managers.aspx Claburn, Thomas (2010) ''Software engineers doubt competence of Managers''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100915030042/http://informationweek.in/Software/10-06-28/Software_engineers_doubt_competence_of_Managers.aspx |date=2010-09-15 }} ''informationweek.in'', accessed on 1 October 2012</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.computerworld.pl/artykuly/350726_1/Mity.i.fakty.html|title=Mity i fakty|author=Andrzej Gontarz|date=2009-10-06|website=computerworld.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2010-01-25}}</ref> and other [[knowledge workers]].<ref>Jemielniak, Dariusz (2012), [https://books.google.com/books?id=QZPpdB_yfqgC ''The New Knowledge Workers''], Cheltenham, UK \u2013 Northampton, USA: Edward Elgar Publishing, {{ISBN|978-1-84844-753-0}}.</ref> He has also published articles on organisational changes in higher education facilities<ref>{{cite journal|last=Jemielniak|first=Dariusz|last2=Greenwood|first2=Davydd J.|title=Wake Up or Perish: Neo-Liberalism, the Social Sciences, and Salvaging the Public University|url=http://csc.sagepub.com/content/early/2013/12/20/1532708613516430.abstract|journal=Cultural Studies \u2194 Critical Methodologies|doi=10.1177/1532708613516430}}</ref> and is an active participant in the debate on the reform of higher education in Poland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forumakademickie.pl/fa/2011/01/reforma-obok-nauki/|title=Reforma obok nauki|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2011-01-01|publisher=Forum Akademickie|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110105411/http://forumakademickie.pl/fa/2011/01/reforma-obok-nauki/|archive-date=2014-01-10|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,75968,8863935,Doktorat_w_ubikacji_.html|title=Doktorat w ubikacji?|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2010-12-23|publisher=wyborcza.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rp.pl/artykul/558363.html|title=Bezkonkurencyjna reforma|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2011-11-03|publisher=rp.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polityka.pl/nauka/czlowiek/1566353,1,uzdrawiamy-szkolnictwo-wyzsze.read|title=Grzeszna reforma|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2014-01-08|publisher=polityka.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Wikimedia ===\nWithin the Wikimedia movement, Jemielniak is involved in the [[Polish Wikipedia]], where he serves as an administrator, bureaucrat and check-user.<ref name=\":0\" /> He was also a steward for all Wikimedia projects.<ref name=\":0\" /> He is a member of the [[Wikimedia Polska|Polish chapter of Wikimedia]], but has never held any roles or position in it.\n\nDariusz has voiced his support for the enabling of [[Conflict-of-interest editing on Wikipedia|paid editing of Wikipedia]], under certain constraints<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/via/why-wikipedia-needs-paid-editing/|title=Why Wikipedia needs paid editing|date=2013-12-16|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref> and has been vocal about reducing the bureaucracy within projects.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/technology/2014/06/wikipedias-bureaucracy-problem-and-how-to-fix-it.html|title=How to Fix Wikipedia's Bureaucracy Problem: Ignore All the Rules|last=Jemielniak|first=Dariusz|date=2014-06-23|website=Slate Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.superstacja.tv/Wiadomosc/Polak_We_Wladzach_Wikipedii_Prof_Dariusz_Jemielniak_W_Programie_Raport,1452968/Polecane/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620120932/http://www.superstacja.tv/Wiadomosc/Polak_We_Wladzach_Wikipedii_Prof_Dariusz_Jemielniak_W_Programie_Raport,1452968/Polecane/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2015-06-20|title=Polak we w\u0142adzach Wikipedii. Prof. Dariusz Jemielniak w programie Raport|date=2015-06-20|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref> He is an advocate of wider involvement of women and academics in the Wikimedia movement<ref>{{cite web| url = http://wyborcza.pl/1,135424,18119626,Prof__Jemielniak___Nie_kazdy_musi_miec_haslo_w_Wikipedii_.html | title = Prof. Jemielniak: \"Nie ka\u017cdy musi mie\u0107 has\u0142o w Wikipedii\" | publisher= wyborcza.pl | accessdate = 2015-06-14|language=pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url =https://chronicle.com/article/Wikipedia-a-Professors-Best/149337 | title = Wikipedia, a Professor's Best Friend | author = Dariusz Jemielniak | accessdate = 2014-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rdc.pl/podcast/popoludnie-rdc-wikipedii-nie-interesuje-prawda-ale-dobrze-uzrodlowiona-informacja/|title=Popo\u0142udnie RDC: \"Wikipedii nie interesuje prawda, ale dobrze u\u017ar\u00f3d\u0142owiona informacja\"|website=Warszawa i Mazowsze - najnowsze wiadomo\u015bci w RDC|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://wyborcza.pl/1,75478,18120510,Nie_kazdy_trafi_do_Wikipedii.html | title = Nie ka\u017cdy trafi do Wikipedii | publisher = wyborcza.pl | author = Justyna Suchecka | accessdate = 2015-06-15|language=pl}}</ref>, and the need to start actively promoting its use and development in academia<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Jemielniak|first=Dariusz|date=2019-12-01|title=Wikipedia: Why is the common knowledge resource still neglected by academics?|url=https://academic.oup.com/gigascience/article/8/12/giz139/5651107|journal=GigaScience|language=en|volume=8|issue=12|doi=10.1093/gigascience/giz139|pmid=31794014|pmc=6889752}}</ref>.\n\nHe has authored a book on the [[social organization]] of Wikipedia, titled ''[[Common Knowledge?: An Ethnography of Wikipedia]],'' (first published in Poland in 2013 as ''\u017bycie wirtualnych dzikich. Netnografia Wikipedii, najwi\u0119kszego projektu wsp\u00f3\u0142tworzonego przez ludzi''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.poltext.pl/b1342-Zycie-wirtualnych-dzikich.htm|title=\u017bycie wirtualnych dzikich|publisher=Poltext|language=pl|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref>), following a period of research on identity and roles in [[Open-source model|open source]] projects, in the form of participating ethnography.<ref>Hamann, Mathias (2010) [http://www.spiegel.de/netzwelt/web/0,1518,706001,00.html ''Wikipedia ist wie \"World of Warcraft\"''] [[Der Spiegel]] (spiegel.de) accessed on 1 October 2012</ref><ref>Cohen, Noam (2010) [https://www.nytimes.com/2010/07/12/business/media/12link.html?_r=1 ''How Can Wikipedia Grow? Maybe in Bengali''], The New York Times (nytimes.com), accessed on 1 October 2012</ref> The book was well-received by critics and other scholars.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Collins|first=Samuel Gerald|date=July 2015|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia by Dariusz Jemielniak. Stanford, CA: Stanford University Press, 2014.|journal=Anthropology of Work Review|language=en|volume=36|issue=1|pages=47\u201348|doi=10.1111/awr.12062}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bourne|first=Dorota Joanna|date=2016|title=All That We Know Dariusz Jemielniak Common knowledge? An ethnography of Wikipedia. (Stanford University Press 2014)|journal=European Management Review|language=en|volume=13|issue=1|pages=69\u201372|doi=10.1111/emre.12067|issn=1740-4762}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://motherboard.vice.com/read/an-ethnography-of-wikipedia|title=An Ethnographic Study of the Wikipedia Hive Mind|last=Kiberd|first=Roisin|date=2 September 2014|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/blogs/library-babel-fish/common-knowledge-jemielniak-wikipeda|title=Common Knowledge: Jemielniak on Wikipeda|last=Fister|first=Barbara|date=11 December 2014|work=[[Inside Higher Ed]]|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://psmag.com/social-justice/killed-wikipedia-93777|title=Who Killed Wikipedia? - Pacific Standard|last=Postrel|first=Virginia|date=17 November 2014|work=[[Pacific Standard]]|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Konieczny|first=Piotr|date=2016-07-09|title=Book Review: Dariusz Jemielniak, Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia|journal=Journal of Sociology|language=en-US|volume=52|issue=3|pages=608\u2013610|doi=10.1177/1440783315590921|issn=1440-7833}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Allen|first=Barry|date=2016-12-31|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia by Dariusz Jemielniak (review)|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/644166|journal=Common Knowledge|language=en|volume=23|issue=1|pages=104|issn=1538-4578|doi=10.1215/0961754X-3692492}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|date=2016-03-14|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia|journal=Qualitative Research in Organizations and Management|volume=11|issue=1|pages=84\u201386|doi=10.1108/QROM-02-2016-1362|issn=1746-5648|url=https://research.tees.ac.uk/ws/files/6772507/596348.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|date=2015-03-01|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia, Dariusz Jemielniak, Stanford University Press, Stanford, CA (2014), 293 pp.|journal=Scandinavian Journal of Management|language=en|volume=31|issue=1|pages=159\u2013161|doi=10.1016/j.scaman.2014.09.006|issn=0956-5221}}</ref>\n\n== Selected academic publications ==\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz i Latusek, Dominika (2005), ''Zarz\u0105dzanie \u2013 teoria i praktyka od podstaw'', Warszawa: WSPiZ, {{ISBN|83-89437-50-3}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and [[Andrzej Ko\u017ami\u0144ski|Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K.]] (ed.) (2008), ''Zarz\u0105dzanie wiedz\u0105. Podr\u0119cznik akademicki'', Warszawa: Wydawnictwa Akademickie i Profesjonalne, {{ISBN|978-83-60501-95-5}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K. and Jemielniak, Dariusz (2008), ''Zarz\u0105dzanie od podstaw. Podr\u0119cznik akademicki'', Warszawa: [[Wydawnictwa Akademickie i Profesjonalne]], {{ISBN|978-83-60501-58-0}} <small>(considered the best economics books in the category ''Management and marketing'' during the Economic Press Fair in 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rp.pl/artykul/230555.html|title=Oferta, kt\u00f3ra goni wydarzenia|author=Anita Grochola, Antoni Kowalik|date=2008-12-08|publisher=rp.pl|accessdate=2010-10-22|language=pl}}</ref>)</small>.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2008), ''Praca oparta na wiedzy. Praca w przedsi\u0119biorstwach wiedzy na przyk\u0142adzie organizacji high-tech'' Warszawa: Wydawnictwa Akademickie i Profesjonalne, {{ISBN|978-83-61408-18-5}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and Kociatkiewicz, Jerzy (ed.) (2008), ''Management Practices in High-tech Environments'', Hershey-New York: Information Science Reference, {{ISBN|978-1-60566-176-6}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and Kociatkiewicz, Jerzy (ed.) (2009), ''Handbook of Research on Knowledge-Intensive Organizations'', Hershey-New York: Information Science Reference, {{ISBN|978-1-60566-176-6}}.\n* A. K. \u041a\u043e\u0437\u044c\u043c\u0438\u043d\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438, \u0412. \u041f. \u0411\u0443\u044f\u043d\u043e\u0432, \u0414. \u0415\u043c\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044f\u043a, A. A. \u0425\u0430\u0447\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u043e\u0432 (2010), ''\u041e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b \u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f. \u0423\u0447\u0435\u0431\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0432\u044b\u0441\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0443\u0447\u0435\u0431\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439'' Moscow: \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0410\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043c\u0438\u044f \u042d\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430 {{ISBN|5-901770-02-1}}.\n* Chrostowski, Aleksander and Jemielniak, Dariusz (2011), ''Skuteczne doradztwo strategiczne: metoda Action Research w praktyce'', Warszawa: Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-180-9}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2012), ''The New Knowledge Workers'', Cheltenham, UK \u2013 Northampton, USA: Edward Elgar Publishing, {{ISBN|978-1-84844-753-0}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and Marks, Abigail (ed.) (2012), ''Managing Dynamic Technology-Oriented Businesses: High-Tech Organizations and Workplaces'', Hershey-New York: Information Science Reference, {{ISBN|978-1-4666-1836-7}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2012) ''Badania jako\u015bciowe. Podej\u015bcia i teorie'', Warszawa: [[Wydawnictwo Naukowe PWN]], {{ISBN|978-83-01-16945-9}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2012) ''Badania jako\u015bciowe. Metody i narz\u0119dzia'', Warszawa: Wydawnictwo Naukowe PWN, {{ISBN|978-83-01-16946-6}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2013) ''\u017bycie wirtualnych dzikich: netnografia Wikipedii, najwi\u0119kszego projektu wsp\u00f3\u0142tworzonego przez ludzi'', Warszawa, Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-285-1}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K. and Jemielniak, Dariusz (2013) ''The New Principles of Management'', Frankfurt \u2013 New York \u2013 Oxford: Peter Lang, {{ISBN|978-3-631-64252-8}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K., Jemielniak, Dariusz, Jendrych, El\u017cbieta, and  Wi\u015bniewska, Halina (2014)  ''Management matters'', Warszawa:  Wolters Kluwer {{ISBN|9788326431807}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K., Jemielniak, Dariusz, and  Latusek-Jurczak, Dominika (2014)  ''Zasady zarz\u0105dzania'', Warszawa:  Wolters Kluwer {{ISBN|978-83-264-3396-2}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2014)  ''Legal Professions at the Crossroads'', New York:  Peter Lang {{ISBN|978-3-631-64385-3}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2014)  ''The Laws of the Knowledge Workplace'', Farnham \u2013 Burlington:  Gower (Ashgate) {{ISBN|978-1-4724-2388-7}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2014) ''Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia'', Stanford: Stanford University Press, {{ISBN|978-0-8047-8944-8}} \n*Jemielniak, Dariusz and Latusek-Jurczak, Dominika (2015) ''Zarz\u0105dzanie. Teoria i praktyka w pigu\u0142ce'', Warszawa: Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-399-5}}.\n*Jemielniak, Dariusz, Latusek-Jurczak, Dominika, and Prystupa-Rz\u0105dca, Kaja (2016) ''Klasyka teorii zarz\u0105dzania', Warszawa: Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-591-3}}.\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Dariusz Jemielniak}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n\n{{Wikimedia Foundation}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jemielniak, Dariusz}}\n[[Category:Polish sociologists]]\n[[Category:Fulbright Scholars]]\n[[Category:Fellows of Collegium Invisibile]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Wikimedia Foundation Board of Trustees members]]\n[[Category:People from Warsaw]]\n[[Category:Polish Wikimedians]]\n[[Category:Wikipedia people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox scientist\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name        = Dariusz Jemielniak\n| honorific_suffix =\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image       = Dr. Dariusz Jemielniak.jpg\n| image_size  = \n| alt         = Dariusz Jemielniak\n| caption     = Jemielniak in 2015\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1975|03|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]]\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| death_cause = \n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates =\n| other_names = \n| residence   = \n| citizenship = \n| nationality = [[Polish people|Polish]]\n| fields      = [[Economics]]\n| workplaces  = [[Kozminski University]]\n| patrons     = \n| education   = \n| alma_mater  = \n| thesis_title =        <!--(or  | thesis1_title =  and  | thesis2_title = )-->\n| thesis_url  =         <!--(or  | thesis1_url  =   and  | thesis2_url  =  )-->\n| thesis_year =         <!--(or  | thesis1_year =   and  | thesis2_year =  )-->\n| doctoral_advisor =    <!--(or  | doctoral_advisors = )-->\n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students = \n| known_for   = \n| influences  = \n| influenced  = \n| awards      = \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| spouse      =         <!--(or | spouses = )-->\n| partner     =         <!--(or | partners = )-->\n| children    = \n| signature   =         <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt = \n| website     = {{URL|www.jemielniak.org}}\n| footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''Dariusz Jemielniak''' (born March 17, 1975) is a full professor of management, the head of the Center for Research on Organizations and Workplaces (CROW), and a founder of New Research on Digital Societies (NeRDS) group at [[Kozminski University]]. His interests revolve about [[critical management studies]], [[open collaboration]] projects (such as [[Wikipedia]] or [[F/LOSS]]), [[narrativity]], [[storytelling]], [[knowledge-intensive organizations]], [[virtual communities]], organizational archetypes, all studied by interpretive and qualitative methods.<ref>[http://crow.kozminski.edu.pl/?page_id=10 ''About us. Dariusz Jemielniak''] CROW website, accessed on 1 October 2012</ref> In 2015, he was elected to the [[Wikimedia Foundation]] board of trustees.\n\n== Career ==\nHe is a graduate of [[VI Liceum Og\u00f3lnokszta\u0142c\u0105ce im. Tadeusza Reytana w Warszawie]] and a 2000 ''[[Cum laude|summa cum laude]]'' graduate from the Faculty of Management, [[Warsaw University]]. In 2004 he earned a Ph.D. in economics from the [[Kozminski University]], under the supervision of [[Andrzej Ko\u017ami\u0144ski]]. In 2014, he received his [[Professor]]'s degree from the [[President of Poland]].\n\nHe has researched and published books in the field of work-space studies; about [[IT professionals]]<ref>[http://www.informationweek.in/Software/10-06-28/Software_engineers_doubt_competence_of_Managers.aspx Claburn, Thomas (2010) ''Software engineers doubt competence of Managers''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100915030042/http://informationweek.in/Software/10-06-28/Software_engineers_doubt_competence_of_Managers.aspx |date=2010-09-15 }} ''informationweek.in'', accessed on 1 October 2012</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.computerworld.pl/artykuly/350726_1/Mity.i.fakty.html|title=Mity i fakty|author=Andrzej Gontarz|date=2009-10-06|website=computerworld.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2010-01-25}}</ref> and other [[knowledge workers]].<ref>Jemielniak, Dariusz (2012), [https://books.google.com/books?id=QZPpdB_yfqgC ''The New Knowledge Workers''], Cheltenham, UK \u2013 Northampton, USA: Edward Elgar Publishing, {{ISBN|978-1-84844-753-0}}.</ref> He has also published articles on organisational changes in higher education facilities<ref>{{cite journal|last=Jemielniak|first=Dariusz|last2=Greenwood|first2=Davydd J.|title=Wake Up or Perish: Neo-Liberalism, the Social Sciences, and Salvaging the Public University|url=http://csc.sagepub.com/content/early/2013/12/20/1532708613516430.abstract|journal=Cultural Studies \u2194 Critical Methodologies|doi=10.1177/1532708613516430}}</ref> and is an active participant in the debate on the reform of higher education in Poland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forumakademickie.pl/fa/2011/01/reforma-obok-nauki/|title=Reforma obok nauki|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2011-01-01|publisher=Forum Akademickie|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110105411/http://forumakademickie.pl/fa/2011/01/reforma-obok-nauki/|archive-date=2014-01-10|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wyborcza.pl/1,75968,8863935,Doktorat_w_ubikacji_.html|title=Doktorat w ubikacji?|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2010-12-23|publisher=wyborcza.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rp.pl/artykul/558363.html|title=Bezkonkurencyjna reforma|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2011-11-03|publisher=rp.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polityka.pl/nauka/czlowiek/1566353,1,uzdrawiamy-szkolnictwo-wyzsze.read|title=Grzeszna reforma|author=Dariusz Jemielniak|date=2014-01-08|publisher=polityka.pl|language=pl|accessdate=2013-01-10}}</ref>\n\n=== Wikimedia ===\nWithin the Wikimedia movement, Jemielniak is involved in the [[Polish Wikipedia]], where he serves as an administrator, bureaucrat and check-user.<ref name=\":0\" /> He was also a steward for all Wikimedia projects.<ref name=\":0\" /> He is a member of the [[Wikimedia Polska|Polish chapter of Wikimedia]], but has never held any roles or position in it.\n\nDariusz has voiced his support for the enabling of [[Conflict-of-interest editing on Wikipedia|paid editing of Wikipedia]], under certain constraints<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/via/why-wikipedia-needs-paid-editing/|title=Why Wikipedia needs paid editing|date=2013-12-16|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref> and has been vocal about reducing the bureaucracy within projects.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/technology/2014/06/wikipedias-bureaucracy-problem-and-how-to-fix-it.html|title=How to Fix Wikipedia's Bureaucracy Problem: Ignore All the Rules|last=Jemielniak|first=Dariusz|date=2014-06-23|website=Slate Magazine|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.superstacja.tv/Wiadomosc/Polak_We_Wladzach_Wikipedii_Prof_Dariusz_Jemielniak_W_Programie_Raport,1452968/Polecane/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620120932/http://www.superstacja.tv/Wiadomosc/Polak_We_Wladzach_Wikipedii_Prof_Dariusz_Jemielniak_W_Programie_Raport,1452968/Polecane/index.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=2015-06-20|title=Polak we w\u0142adzach Wikipedii. Prof. Dariusz Jemielniak w programie Raport|date=2015-06-20|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref> He is an advocate of wider involvement of women and academics in the Wikimedia movement<ref>{{cite web| url = http://wyborcza.pl/1,135424,18119626,Prof__Jemielniak___Nie_kazdy_musi_miec_haslo_w_Wikipedii_.html | title = Prof. Jemielniak: \"Nie ka\u017cdy musi mie\u0107 has\u0142o w Wikipedii\" | publisher= wyborcza.pl | accessdate = 2015-06-14|language=pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url =https://chronicle.com/article/Wikipedia-a-Professors-Best/149337 | title = Wikipedia, a Professor's Best Friend | author = Dariusz Jemielniak | accessdate = 2014-10-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rdc.pl/podcast/popoludnie-rdc-wikipedii-nie-interesuje-prawda-ale-dobrze-uzrodlowiona-informacja/|title=Popo\u0142udnie RDC: \"Wikipedii nie interesuje prawda, ale dobrze u\u017ar\u00f3d\u0142owiona informacja\"|website=Warszawa i Mazowsze - najnowsze wiadomo\u015bci w RDC|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://wyborcza.pl/1,75478,18120510,Nie_kazdy_trafi_do_Wikipedii.html | title = Nie ka\u017cdy trafi do Wikipedii | publisher = wyborcza.pl | author = Justyna Suchecka | accessdate = 2015-06-15|language=pl}}</ref>, and the need to start actively promoting its use and development in academia<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Jemielniak|first=Dariusz|date=2019-12-01|title=Wikipedia: Why is the common knowledge resource still neglected by academics?|url=https://academic.oup.com/gigascience/article/8/12/giz139/5651107|journal=GigaScience|language=en|volume=8|issue=12|doi=10.1093/gigascience/giz139|pmid=31794014|pmc=6889752}}</ref>.\n\nHe has authored a book on the [[social organization]] of Wikipedia, titled ''[[Common Knowledge?: An Ethnography of Wikipedia]],'' (first published in Poland in 2013 as ''\u017bycie wirtualnych dzikich. Netnografia Wikipedii, najwi\u0119kszego projektu wsp\u00f3\u0142tworzonego przez ludzi''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.poltext.pl/b1342-Zycie-wirtualnych-dzikich.htm|title=\u017bycie wirtualnych dzikich|publisher=Poltext|language=pl|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref>), following a period of research on identity and roles in [[Open-source model|open source]] projects, in the form of participating ethnography.<ref>Hamann, Mathias (2010) [http://www.spiegel.de/netzwelt/web/0,1518,706001,00.html ''Wikipedia ist wie \"World of Warcraft\"''] [[Der Spiegel]] (spiegel.de) accessed on 1 October 2012</ref><ref>Cohen, Noam (2010) [https://www.nytimes.com/2010/07/12/business/media/12link.html?_r=1 ''How Can Wikipedia Grow? Maybe in Bengali''], The New York Times (nytimes.com), accessed on 1 October 2012</ref> The book was well-received by critics and other scholars.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Collins|first=Samuel Gerald|date=July 2015|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia by Dariusz Jemielniak. Stanford, CA: Stanford University Press, 2014.|journal=Anthropology of Work Review|language=en|volume=36|issue=1|pages=47\u201348|doi=10.1111/awr.12062}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bourne|first=Dorota Joanna|date=2016|title=All That We Know Dariusz Jemielniak Common knowledge? An ethnography of Wikipedia. (Stanford University Press 2014)|journal=European Management Review|language=en|volume=13|issue=1|pages=69\u201372|doi=10.1111/emre.12067|issn=1740-4762}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://motherboard.vice.com/read/an-ethnography-of-wikipedia|title=An Ethnographic Study of the Wikipedia Hive Mind|last=Kiberd|first=Roisin|date=2 September 2014|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/blogs/library-babel-fish/common-knowledge-jemielniak-wikipeda|title=Common Knowledge: Jemielniak on Wikipeda|last=Fister|first=Barbara|date=11 December 2014|work=[[Inside Higher Ed]]|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://psmag.com/social-justice/killed-wikipedia-93777|title=Who Killed Wikipedia? - Pacific Standard|last=Postrel|first=Virginia|date=17 November 2014|work=[[Pacific Standard]]|accessdate=8 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Konieczny|first=Piotr|date=2016-07-09|title=Book Review: Dariusz Jemielniak, Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia|journal=Journal of Sociology|language=en-US|volume=52|issue=3|pages=608\u2013610|doi=10.1177/1440783315590921|issn=1440-7833}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Allen|first=Barry|date=2016-12-31|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia by Dariusz Jemielniak (review)|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/644166|journal=Common Knowledge|language=en|volume=23|issue=1|pages=104|issn=1538-4578|doi=10.1215/0961754X-3692492}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|date=2016-03-14|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia|journal=Qualitative Research in Organizations and Management|volume=11|issue=1|pages=84\u201386|doi=10.1108/QROM-02-2016-1362|issn=1746-5648|url=https://research.tees.ac.uk/ws/files/6772507/596348.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|date=2015-03-01|title=Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia, Dariusz Jemielniak, Stanford University Press, Stanford, CA (2014), 293 pp.|journal=Scandinavian Journal of Management|language=en|volume=31|issue=1|pages=159\u2013161|doi=10.1016/j.scaman.2014.09.006|issn=0956-5221}}</ref>\n\n== Selected academic publications ==\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz i Latusek, Dominika (2005), ''Zarz\u0105dzanie \u2013 teoria i praktyka od podstaw'', Warszawa: WSPiZ, {{ISBN|83-89437-50-3}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and [[Andrzej Ko\u017ami\u0144ski|Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K.]] (ed.) (2008), ''Zarz\u0105dzanie wiedz\u0105. Podr\u0119cznik akademicki'', Warszawa: Wydawnictwa Akademickie i Profesjonalne, {{ISBN|978-83-60501-95-5}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K. and Jemielniak, Dariusz (2008), ''Zarz\u0105dzanie od podstaw. Podr\u0119cznik akademicki'', Warszawa: [[Wydawnictwa Akademickie i Profesjonalne]], {{ISBN|978-83-60501-58-0}} <small>(considered the best economics books in the category ''Management and marketing'' during the Economic Press Fair in 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rp.pl/artykul/230555.html|title=Oferta, kt\u00f3ra goni wydarzenia|author=Anita Grochola, Antoni Kowalik|date=2008-12-08|publisher=rp.pl|accessdate=2010-10-22|language=pl}}</ref>)</small>.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2008), ''Praca oparta na wiedzy. Praca w przedsi\u0119biorstwach wiedzy na przyk\u0142adzie organizacji high-tech'' Warszawa: Wydawnictwa Akademickie i Profesjonalne, {{ISBN|978-83-61408-18-5}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and Kociatkiewicz, Jerzy (ed.) (2008), ''Management Practices in High-tech Environments'', Hershey-New York: Information Science Reference, {{ISBN|978-1-60566-176-6}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and Kociatkiewicz, Jerzy (ed.) (2009), ''Handbook of Research on Knowledge-Intensive Organizations'', Hershey-New York: Information Science Reference, {{ISBN|978-1-60566-176-6}}.\n* A. K. \u041a\u043e\u0437\u044c\u043c\u0438\u043d\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0438, \u0412. \u041f. \u0411\u0443\u044f\u043d\u043e\u0432, \u0414. \u0415\u043c\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044f\u043a, A. A. \u0425\u0430\u0447\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u043e\u0432 (2010), ''\u041e\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b \u0443\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f. \u0423\u0447\u0435\u0431\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0432\u044b\u0441\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0443\u0447\u0435\u0431\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0439'' Moscow: \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0410\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043c\u0438\u044f \u042d\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0430 {{ISBN|5-901770-02-1}}.\n* Chrostowski, Aleksander and Jemielniak, Dariusz (2011), ''Skuteczne doradztwo strategiczne: metoda Action Research w praktyce'', Warszawa: Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-180-9}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2012), ''The New Knowledge Workers'', Cheltenham, UK \u2013 Northampton, USA: Edward Elgar Publishing, {{ISBN|978-1-84844-753-0}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz and Marks, Abigail (ed.) (2012), ''Managing Dynamic Technology-Oriented Businesses: High-Tech Organizations and Workplaces'', Hershey-New York: Information Science Reference, {{ISBN|978-1-4666-1836-7}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2012) ''Badania jako\u015bciowe. Podej\u015bcia i teorie'', Warszawa: [[Wydawnictwo Naukowe PWN]], {{ISBN|978-83-01-16945-9}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2012) ''Badania jako\u015bciowe. Metody i narz\u0119dzia'', Warszawa: Wydawnictwo Naukowe PWN, {{ISBN|978-83-01-16946-6}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2013) ''\u017bycie wirtualnych dzikich: netnografia Wikipedii, najwi\u0119kszego projektu wsp\u00f3\u0142tworzonego przez ludzi'', Warszawa, Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-285-1}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K. and Jemielniak, Dariusz (2013) ''The New Principles of Management'', Frankfurt \u2013 New York \u2013 Oxford: Peter Lang, {{ISBN|978-3-631-64252-8}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K., Jemielniak, Dariusz, Jendrych, El\u017cbieta, and  Wi\u015bniewska, Halina (2014)  ''Management matters'', Warszawa:  Wolters Kluwer {{ISBN|9788326431807}}.\n* Ko\u017ami\u0144ski, Andrzej K., Jemielniak, Dariusz, and  Latusek-Jurczak, Dominika (2014)  ''Zasady zarz\u0105dzania'', Warszawa:  Wolters Kluwer {{ISBN|978-83-264-3396-2}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2014)  ''Legal Professions at the Crossroads'', New York:  Peter Lang {{ISBN|978-3-631-64385-3}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (ed.) (2014)  ''The Laws of the Knowledge Workplace'', Farnham \u2013 Burlington:  Gower (Ashgate) {{ISBN|978-1-4724-2388-7}}.\n* Jemielniak, Dariusz (2014) ''Common Knowledge? An Ethnography of Wikipedia'', Stanford: Stanford University Press, {{ISBN|978-0-8047-8944-8}} \n*Jemielniak, Dariusz and Latusek-Jurczak, Dominika (2015) ''Zarz\u0105dzanie. Teoria i praktyka w pigu\u0142ce'', Warszawa: Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-399-5}}.\n*Jemielniak, Dariusz, Latusek-Jurczak, Dominika, and Prystupa-Rz\u0105dca, Kaja (2016) ''Klasyka teorii zarz\u0105dzania', Warszawa: Poltext, {{ISBN|978-83-7561-591-3}}.\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Dariusz Jemielniak}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n\n{{Wikimedia Foundation}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jemielniak, Dariusz}}\n[[Category:Polish sociologists]]\n[[Category:Fulbright Scholars]]\n[[Category:Fellows of Collegium Invisibile]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Wikimedia Foundation Board of Trustees members]]\n[[Category:People from Warsaw]]\n[[Category:Polish Wikimedians]]\n[[Category:Wikipedia people]]\n", "name_user": "84.0.193.147", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dariusz_Jemielniak"}
